FBIS3-23436 "jptot013__l94117" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 20 March 1994 WEST EUROPE CYPRUS Chairman of Solidarity Committee With Kurdistan Murdered Shot Outside Apartment NC2003220294 Nicosia CyBC Television Network in Greek 2138 GMT 20 Mar 94 NC2003220294 Nicosia CyBC Television Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Unscheduled news flash] [Text] It has just been announced that Theofilos Yeoryiadhis, 37, a turkologist and chairman of the Committee of Solidarity with Kurdistan, was murdered in Nicosia tonight. Yeoryiadhis was shot in the parking lot of a three-story building on Thoukidhidhou Street in Aglanja where he lived with his family. According to a female witness living at a nearby house, two people were seen escaping on a motorcycle immediately after the shooting. The area has been blocked off by police and the police chief and director of the criminal investigation department are there. Yeoryiadhis is the father of three children aged 13, eight, and 10 months.
